This project is testing the http://automationpractice.com/index.php
• There are 2 functionalities you should be testing.
• Test these 2 functionalities with TestNG, Selenium and Java.
• You should have a Base Driver class where you set up your WebDriver.(You should
provide driver type(chrome-firefox) as a @Parameter to your @BeforeMethod)
• You should implement PAGE OBJECT MODEL into your project(create page classes)
• Run your Tests from TestNG.xml
• Contact Us Test and PlaceOrder Test should be in Regression group
• Use explicit wait as much as you can!
Try to not use Thread.sleep.(You will need a lot of waits for this website!
BE CAREFUL :))
• Pre-Condition: Create an account on the page before starting to automate and
use that account for automation.


SCENARIO 1 | Contact Us Functionality Test:

- You should navigate to the website and login to your account.
- You should test this functionality with 3 different input (use @Parameters to send test data)


SCENARIO 2 - Place an Order:

-You should navigate to the website and login to your account.
- You should select a product from HomePage and add to cart
- You should complete proceed to checkout process
- At the end you should verify success message
- Also you’ll see order reference value at the end, you should verify that value from “My Orders”
page